The paper discusses the creation and growth of arXiv.org, which is a preprint server for scientific articles in various fields, including computer science. The paper specifically mentions the sharing of drafts of articles by physicists, which suggests that the computer science sub-categories most likely to be relevant are those related to information retrieval (cs.IR), digital libraries (cs.DL), cybersecurity (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
